.TH "tb_ctl_alloc" 9 "tb_ctl_alloc" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
tb_ctl_alloc \- allocate a control channel
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "struct tb_ctl *" tb_ctl_alloc
.BI "(struct tb_nhi *nhi "  ","
.BI "event_cb cb "  ","
.BI "void *cb_data "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "nhi" 12
Pointer to NHI
.IP "cb" 12
Callback called for plug events
.IP "cb_data" 12
Data passed to \fIcb\fP
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
cb will be invoked once for every hot plug event.
.SH "RETURN"
Returns a pointer on success or NULL on failure.
